-            CRecipient recipient = {scriptPubKey, rcp.amount, rcp.fSubtractFeeFromAmount};
+            CRecipient recipient{CNoDestination{scriptPubKey}, rcp.amount, rcp.fSubtractFeeFromAmount};

comments.body:
We know the destination here. Otherwise we wouldn't be able to decode it from the string (the `validateAddress()` check that is performed above would fail). This should be:
```c++
CTxDestination dest = DecodeDestination(rcp.address.toStdString());
CRecipient recipient = {dest, rcp.amount, rcp.fSubtractFeeFromAmount};
```

This fixes https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/28246#discussion_r1371640502.

